<h3 id="what-yeoman-can-do">What YEOMAN can do?</h3>

<p>Instead of downloading web development frameworks all the time you started a project, It can be done in a few terimal commands.</p>

<p>YEOMAN has <em><a href="http://yeoman.io/generators/" target="_blank">generators</a></em> ecosystem which automates the process of creating containers and including dependencies for your new projects.</p>

<h3 id="installation">Installation</h3>

<p>I wish you have Node and its package manager. If you donâ€™t, please see at <a href="https://www.npmjs.org/" target="_blank">npm</a></p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nv">$ </span>npm <span class="nb">install</span> <span class="nt">-g</span> yo grunt-cli bower</code></pre></figure>

<p>Now, things are ready to go. Letâ€™s start a simple web applicaiton with it.</p>

<h3 id="literally-getting-started">Literally Getting started</h3>

<p>To get started a project with YEOMAN, you needs to install a generator of your choice.</p>

<p>This will install the simple <a href="https://github.com/yeoman/generator-webapp" target="_blank">web-application</a> generator.</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nv">$ </span>npm <span class="nb">install</span> <span class="nt">-g</span> generator-webapp</code></pre></figure>

<p>Make a folder and initialize yo like this:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nv">$ </span><span class="nb">mkdir </span>your_project <span class="o">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class="nb">cd </span>your_project
<span class="nv">$ </span>yo webapp</code></pre></figure>

<p>Basically,it will set up HTMLBiolerplate, JQuery and Grunt config file. 
For css frameworks, you can choose one framework of your choice (bootstrap, Sass, Modernizr).</p>

<p>This is how the directory looks like at this stage.</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">â”œâ”€â”€ app <span class="c">#your app goes here</span>
